i believe you can get an m performance package for the bmw 4-door.

it's just the aero package and suspension and seat nothing else. the m235i is the complete package extra hp, larger brakes and extra suspension parts. the mppk can be had for the bmw. but that doesn't add the extra suspension items or larger brakes.

i was in the prague airport several years ago and there was a skoda on display -- did a double take, it was a volkswagen without any of the volkswagen logos, etc. now, the car was roped off, so i really couldn't peek inside to see if the interior was also a volkswagen, but, whatever differences there were, were minor.

i assume skoda's are priced lower than volkswagen's and volkswagen's of course are priced lower than audis, etc.

while watching motorweek's test of the lambo aventador sv, i noticed the "console" was pretty much the same as the mmi+ that i have in my 2014 s4. even the knobs and switches were straight out of an audi (that would be priced several hundred thousand dollars less.)

